full_summary:
Government Tender Announcement
=====================================================

### Notice Title

Recipient Audits for Canadian Coast Guard Auxiliaries

### Reference Number and Amendment Number

* PW-22-01014142
* Amendment Number: 1

### Solicitation Details

* Solicitation Number: 30003703
* Publication Date: 2022-11-24
* Tender Closing Date: 2022-12-15T14:00:00

### Contract Details

* Expected Contract Start Date: None
* Expected Contract End Date: None
* Tender Status: Expired

### Trade Agreements

This tender is open to suppliers under the following trade agreements:

* Canada-UK Trade Continuity Agreement (Canada-UK TCA)
* Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership (CPTPP)
* Canada-Ukraine Free Trade Agreement (CUFTA)
* World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA)
* Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA)
* Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
* Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA)
* Canada-European Union Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA)
* Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement
* Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA)
* Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-Honduras Free Trade Agreement

### Supply Arrangement

This tender is part of the Professional Audit Support Services (PASS) Supply Arrangement under the following stream:

* Stream 8: Recipient/Contribution Agreement Audits

### Contract Description

Fisheries and Oceans Canada and the Canadian Coast Guard seek to establish a contract for recipient audits of Canadian Coast Guard Auxiliaries in British Columbia and Nova Scotia. The estimated duration of the contract is until 2023-04-10, with a delivery timeframe of up to 2023-03-31.

### Conditions for Participation

This tender is open only to suppliers who are holders of the Professional Audit Support Services (PASS) Supply Arrangement under the specified stream. Suppliers who are not qualified under the stream(s) and category(ies) required must update their supplier profile and provide proof of addition to the Department's procurement officer.

### Point of Contact

For more information, please contact:

* Name: Richard Soulliere
* Email: DFOtenders-soumissionsMPO@dfo-mpo.gc.ca
* Phone: None
* Fax: None
